            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#schwarzfitterJ" start="1274.894" end="x">And in this manner . . . day after day they would take people and beat them. And then [word not clear] there were unfortunately such people who fell in disfavor to the great gentlemen, and they beat them constantly. So we agreed among us that we shall go with a proposal, that daily ten men will report for beatings to sooth their bestial instincts, and to request, that in a <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> of seven hundred people, that on every seventieth days each one would be beaten, and not to beat day in and day out the same people, with the result that they were being beaten to death. Of course, he rejected the proposal. From this <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>, where there were seven hundred people, there remained approximately hundred and three people at the time of the liquidation of the lager.</span>
        </li>
