            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#schwarzfitterJ" start="2348.839" end="x">In the RR-car. At that moment went through our mind the old memories. By that time we were not anymore human beings like we remembered from once at home, because all . . . , all that belonged to the past. But at that moment a man . . . , a man remembered [?] that once there was a home, [where] humans died like humans, and not under such conditions, and such circumstances. No food, no drink, were given to us. Not even swallowing [catching our breath?], standing up was permitted. And so we remained for five days.</span>
        </li>
