            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#schwarzfitterJ" start="2677.195" end="x">The first morning, that was on a Tuesday, the tenth of April, we had the great fortune to get for twelve people one bread of 1,200 grams. For twelve people that means one hundred grams of bread per person. After six days without food. There was no water. It was specially blocked up.</span>
